description:
Sponsor: Hyte Y70 Touch Infinite on Amazon - https://geni.us/yTLj or Hyte Y70 Non-Touch on Amazon - https://geni.us/IgTvHC6
We're visiting Thermal Grizzly's factory to see how thermal paste is made, featuring Roman "Der8auer" Hartung to make Duronaut. This thermal paste deep-dive uses scanning electron microscopes to look at paste particle size, testing equipment to evaluate differences, and machines to manufacture the thermal paste itself. All of this was filmed in Germany, near Berlin, at Thermal Grizzly's new factory. We can finally see how much thermal paste is too much. This video goes into thermal paste differences, how to make thermal paste, good vs bad thermal interface material, and more, all to talk about what cools CPUs and GPUs.

We have a full multi-part series for our Made In Germany Factory Tour videos coming up!

Watch Der8auer's video, "The Secret of Testing Thermal Paste," here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1BfSx5IG42c
TOO MUCH THERMAL PASTE: https://www.youtube.c
title: We Made Perfect Thermal Paste in a Factory, ft. Der8auer | Made In Germany
